      "stem_html": "<p><i>trans</i>-Decalin is more stable than its cis isomer, but <i>cis</i>-bicyclo[4.1.0]heptane is more stable than its trans isomer. Explain.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbDhSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--3328ea5eebb642b28aead60977e575820459efdf/OChem_04_EC_011.jpg\" alt=\"Trans-Decalin has two cyclohexane rings fused together. Cis-Bicyclo[4.1.0]heptane has a cyclohexane ring fused to a cyclopropane ring.\">",
